This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it deals with enhancing the ranking results in entity retrieval tasks. It also involves the use of neural network classifiers, which are commonly used in Natural Language Processing (NLP) tasks, suggesting that it could also belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category. Additionally, the use of supervised machine learning models indicates that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the task involves scoring knowledge base triples, which suggests that it could also belong to the Databases (cs.DB) sub-category.
